Evangelist Davies Ekunola, Coordinator, Genesis Team International, has urged Nigerians to shun the path of injustice, killings, disobedience and other evils The cleric at the Genesis Crusade 2022, tagged, ‘Abraham Heard My Voice’, held recently at the Rehoboth Prayer Mountain, along Papa-Ilaro, Ogun State, said Nigeria was cease faced with setbacks due to high level of wickedness and continued disobedience to God’s instructions. He warned that charity works, offerings, tithes, and other financial contributions by many who go to places of worship do not supersede genuine salvation, which he stressed guarantees heaven. High Praises, Special Prayers At INL Annual Thanksgiving… CAN Debunks Dispute With LASG Over Archbishop’s Residence… He stressed: “You cannot sit on the fence. It is either you obey God or disobey God,” adding that since the fall of Adam at the Garden of Eden, man “has continued to fall into error and until we return to the path of obedience and reconciliation with God, the problems of man will persist.”